<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 21 at 2:51PM EDT until July 21 at 3:15PM EDT by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 315 PM EDT
FOR CENTRAL TROUP COUNTY...
At 250 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near LaGrange,
moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
LaGrange, Mountville, Big Springs, Wares Crossroads, Louise, Baughs
Crossroads and Smiths Crossroad.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
